song.title: Polly

annotations:
Polly, will you ever notice me?
 Sinkin’ in the middle of your sea
 Water in my ears, a wavy melody
 I will hold my breath eternally

Dora wrote this verse after seeing Billie Eilish perform at the 2019 Glastonbury Festival. In a conversation about the song, she revealed she was inspired by the sea of people in the audience and their connection with the singer: “Everyone was mesmerized and I would hear girls saying things like ‘oh my god she looked at me!’. That excitement of connecting, that feeling of being in that energetic sea and hearing the most amazing music and it’s just hitting so good- I think that first verse is that moment”.

album.full_title: comfortably in pain by Dora Jar
album.name: comfortably in pain

annotations:
My heart is a crustacean
 Could you come and crack it open?

The comparison of the heart to a crustacean, although weird, serves to characterize that her heart has hardened, perhaps due to problems in previous relationships. Dora elects to compare her heart to a crustacean rather than something more traditional like a rock mostly to help aid in the alliteration she uses here. (ie: Crustacean, Come, CraCK). It is worthy to note that the repeated C sounds could act as onomatopoeia making sound effects for the cracking of the crustacean/her heart in the song.
